  "markdown": "Anyon Systems Inc. \u00b7 Montr\u00e9al \u00b7 A Canadian quantum company\n[](https://anyonsys.com/en)\n  * Company\n  * Markets\n  * [Products](https://anyonsys.com/en/products)\n  * [Technology](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology)\n  * [News](https://anyonsys.com/en/news)\n  * Careers\n  * FR\n\n\nFR[Contact](https://anyonsys.com/en/contact)\n# Engineering quantum computing for real-world deployment.\nAnyon Systems is building the next generation of quantum computing infrastructure: designed not just for research, but for **real-world deployment**. Founded in Canada in 2014, the company pioneered the country\u2019s **first universal gate-based quantum computers** and continues to advance sovereign quantum capabilities while serving a global market.\n![](https://anyonsys.com/assets/site-images/office-external/office-external-04.jpg?v=cfc17f3)\n![](https://anyonsys.com/assets/site-images/office-external/office-external-11.jpg?v=cfc17f3)\nAnyon Systems has demonstrated its ability to **deliver operational quantum hardware into real-world environments** , including the deployment of its MonarQ system within Calcul Qu\u00e9bec\u2019s HPC ecosystem. Today, the company provides **fully integrated, ready-to-use quantum platforms** that combine hardware, software, and deployment expertise: enabling immediate use by research institutions, government programs, and enterprise partners in high-performance computing environments worldwide.\n## Built for Real Environments\nAnyon Systems designs, builds, and commercializes full-stack superconducting quantum computers for real operational environments.\nAnyon is focused on practical quantum deployment today while engineering the path toward fault-tolerant quantum computing.\n[Explore the technology](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology)\nThe company has already demonstrated the ability to deliver operational quantum hardware into high-performance computing environments, including MonarQ, deployed in Calcul Qu\u00e9bec\u2019s HPC ecosystem.\n[Read the announcement](https://anyonsys.com/en/news)\nAnyon\u2019s approach is built around real systems, real users, and real infrastructure. Not laboratory prototypes alone.\n[The Anyon experience](https://anyonsys.com/en/careers/experience)\n## Anyon\u2019s Core Strengths\n  * Full-stack superconducting quantum computing architecture\n  * Operational quantum hardware deployed in customer environments\n  * Hardware designed for HPC and data centre integration\n  * Multi-tenant quantum / HPC-as-a-service capability\n  * Hardware-level noise resilience to reduce error-correction overhead\n  * Roadmap toward synthetic topological qubits and fault tolerance\n\n\nHelp us build quantum computing for the real world.\n[Explore careers](https://anyonsys.com/en/careers/jobs)\n![Anyon Systems](https://anyonsys.com/assets/logo_pure-white.svg?v=cfc17f3)\nFull-stack superconducting quantum systems. Designed and built in Montr\u00e9al.\n  * [About](https://anyonsys.com/en/company/about)\n  * [News](https://anyonsys.com/en/news)\n  * [Careers](https://anyonsys.com/en/careers/jobs)\n\n\nMontr\u00e9al \u00b7 QC \u00b7 Canada\n[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/anyon-systems-inc-/)\nMarkets\n  * [HPC centres](https://anyonsys.com/en/markets/hpc)\n  * [Government](https://anyonsys.com/en/markets/government)\n  * [Defence](https://anyonsys.com/en/markets/defence)\n  * [Universities](https://anyonsys.com/en/markets/research)\n\n\nProducts\n  * [Qube](https://anyonsys.com/en/products#qube)\n  * [Hudson](https://anyonsys.com/en/products#hudson)\n  * [Snowflurry](https://anyonsys.com/en/products#snowflurry)\n  * [Roadmap](https://anyonsys.com/en/products#roadmap)\n\n\nTechnology\n  * [Quantum processor](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology#quantum-processor)\n  * [Cryogenic system](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology#cryogenic-system)\n  * [Control electronics](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology#control-electronics)\n  * [Software stack](https://anyonsys.com/en/technology#software-stack)\n\n\nResources\n  * [Roadmap](https://anyonsys.com/en/products#roadmap)\n\n\nHead office\nMontr\u00e9al \u00b7 Quebec\n8275 Trans Canada Route A410\nSaint-Laurent, QC H4S 0B6\nQuebec\nBromont \u00b7 Quebec\n45 Bd de l\u2019A\u00e9roport\nBromont, QC J2L 2X4\nQuebec\nSherbrooke \u00b7 Quebec\n3000 Bd de l\u2019Universit\u00e9\nSherbrooke, QC J1K 0A5\nOntario\nWaterloo \u00b7 Ontario\n295 Hagey Blvd #2\nWaterloo, ON N2L 6R5\nUnited Kingdom\nKidlington\nOxford Technology Park, Technology Dr\nKidlington OX5 1GN\nIsrael\nIsrael\nAddress coming soon\n\u00a9 2026 Anyon Systems Inc.\n[Privacy](https://anyonsys.com/en/privacy)[Support](https://anyonsys.com/en/contact)\nTop\n## We use cookies!\nThis website uses cookies to enhance your experience.\nAccept allAccept only necessary\nManage preferences\n[Privacy Policy](https://anyonsys.com/en/privacy)\n",
